Author: TwilightPunkster K64#7533
Content: @FishyGuts but we are not gonna work old fashioned development style at K64.

Author: TwilightPunkster K64#7533
Content: The plan is that I want the future dev team to be Devops. We will have objectives, and who takes one on, takes responsibility of that objective. Instead of useless agile methodology, we will focus on MoSCoW. Must haves, Should haves, Could haves, Wont haves.

Author: TwilightPunkster K64#7533
Content: The blockchain development that will be done in-house at K64, is fairly scoped: the gaming SDK and Infra-added-value. We will mostly work towards the latter through our partner ChainMakers ( @siu - Chainmakers and @jorian ).

Author: Cryptoon#3362
Content: I think the problem is that most people already have their mind made up before diving into the technicalities of projects.

Author: Cryptoon#3362
Content: And they will search for things that coincide with their pre-existing views

Author: Cryptoon#3362
Content: But I see a lot of people that once I start explaining what kmd does and how it works and what you can do using kmd tech, they almost dont believe me because of how advanced it is

Author: Cryptoon#3362
Content: KMD really is the swiss pocket knife of crypto, where a veriblock for example pretends to be 51% protection, or 0x pretends to be a DEX, or XRP pretends to be able to do 20k+ tx/s, kmd can do all of these things and much more

Author: Cryptoon#3362
Content: AND most of the times it can do these things in a far superior manner.

Author: Cryptoon#3362
Content: Slowly but surely I have a feeling more and more people are seeing this, with the rebrand coming and more projects coming over to the fun side, it's only a matter of time before kmd is a top 20 - top 10 project üòÉ
